<li>About how to add local images on blog</li>
</ol>


<p>copy your image in Octopress/source/images.</p>

<p>PS: Octopress(whatever you named it) directory is a repository directory for your blog.</p>

<p>then you can use img tag as</p>

<p><img class="left" src="/images/terminal.png" width="350" height="350" title="image" alt="images"></p>

<p>like</p>

<p><img class="left" src="/images/php.jpg" width="350" height="350" title="image" alt="images"></p>
